ARMOR

Usage       : cast 'armor' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 1, Mage - 3, Bard - 44, Paladin - 87

The Armor spell will improve your AC by 20.

See also: AC
#
BLESS

Usage       : cast 'bless' <victim | object>
Duration    : 6 hours, permanent for objects.
Level       : Cleric - 16, Paladin - 34

Bless on a victim will improve the victims saving throw versus spells
by 1, and furthermore improve the hitroll by 2.

Bless on an item currently has no defined action.  It is only possible
to bless non-evil items, and the object blessed may weigh no more
than five pounds per level of caster. 
#
BLINDNESS

Usage       : cast 'blindness' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 23, Vampyre - 48, Mage - 56

Blindness will blind a victim failing its saving throw.
A blinded person will have -4 penalty to both hitroll and AC.

See also: AC
#
BURNING HANDS

Usage       : cast 'burning hands' <victim>
Level       : Mage - 18

Mage focuses his energy into the tip of their hands thus turning them
into fire.  They can burn the creature they are fighting with their
hands.

See also: CHILL TOUCH
#
CALL LIGHTNING

Usage       : cast 'call lightning' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 62

This spell will use the "force of nature" to make a lightning
strike the victim.  It is therefore only possible to call lightning
outside, and it has to be raining (or worse).

See also: CONTROL WEATHER
#
CAST

Usage: cast '<spell name>' <target>

For "magical" people.  If you want to throw a spell at someone or
something.

Example:

  > cast 'burning hands' <player>
  Note that the name of the spell must be enclosed by "'"s.

See also: help on each individual spell:

Examples:

  > help cure light
  > help harm
  > help energy drain
#
CHARM PERSON

Usage       : cast 'charm person' <victim>
Level       : Mage - 32, Bard - 38, Vampyre - 77

Is is not possible to charm anyone that is already charmed, if
you're charmed yourself, or if the person is higher level than
yourself.  The person will get a saving throw versus "paralysation".

A charmed person will follow you, and not be able to attack you, you
can order the charmed person using the order command.
#
CHILL TOUCH

Usage       : cast 'chill touch' <victim>
Level       : Mage - 9

This spell is more powerful than the magic missile spell.
A victim failing its saving throw will get its strength
reduced by one.

See also: MAGIC MISSILE
#
COLORSPRAY COLOR SPRAY

Usage       : cast 'color spray' <victim>
Level       : Mage - 74

This spell is more powerful than the lightning bolt spell.

See also: LIGHTNING BOLT

For help on actual color, see:  ANSI
#
CONTROL WEATHER

Usage       : cast 'control weather' <'better' | 'worse'>
Level       : Bard - 26, Cleric - 68

This spell will change the "course" of the current weather.

Example:

  > cast 'control weather' worse
#
CREATE FOOD

Usage       : cast 'create food'
Level       : Cleric - 3

This spell instantly creates a fresh waybread.  The waybread will be
filling for the next (5+level) hours, up to a maximum of 24 hours.

See also: CREATE WATER
#
CREATE WATER

Usage       : cast 'create water' <drink container>
Level       : Cleric - 5

Expect disastrous results if cast upon a drink container which contains
another liquid than water.  Empty or water containers will be filled
depending on the level of the caster.

Double amount of water will be created if it is raining (or worse).

See also: CREATE FOOD
#
CURE BLIND

Usage       : cast 'cure blind' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 12

This spell will cure a person blinded by the "blindness" spell, it
can not remove blindness caused by for example cursed items.
#
CURE CRITIC

Usage       : cast 'cure critic' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 35

This spell cures 3d8+3 hitpoints of damage.
#
CURE LIGHT

Usage       : cast 'cure light' <victim>
Level       : Cleric & Paladin - 1

Cures minor wounds and scratches.
#
CURSE

Usage       : cast 'curse' <victim | object>
Duration    : 7 Days, permanent on objects.
Level       : Mage - 82

Curse cast on a person that fails the saving throw, will reduce their
hitroll and damage roll both by one.  It will also reduce the saving
throw versus paralysation by one. 

When cast upon an object, the object will become undropable.
#
DETECT ALIGNMENT

Usage       : cast 'detect alignment'
Duration    : 12 hours + level
Level       : Cleric & Paladin - 9

Allows the caster to detect the alignment of those around them.
Evil will show as a red aura, good in a blue aura.

See also: DETECT INVISIBILITY
#
DETECT INVISIBILITY

Usage       : cast 'detect invisibility' [self]
Duration    : 12 hours + level/4
Level       : Vampyre - 3, Cleric - 9, Bard - 62

This spell enables you to see invisible items and players.
#
DETECT MAGIC

Usage       : cast 'detect magic' [self]
Duration    : 12 hours + level
Level       : Mage - 5

This spell will let you see the magical aura surrounding magical
objects.
#
DETECT POISON

Usage       : cast 'detect poison' <victim | food | drink>
Level       :  Cleric - 7, Bard - 20, Mage - 52, Vampyre - 63

Cast on food or drinks (drink containers) you will be able to
sense if it is poisoned.

Cast on a person you will be able to see if that person is
poisoned.
#
DISPEL EVIL

Usage       : cast 'dispel evil' <victim>
Level       : Paladin - 44, Cleric - 53

This spell will only affect evil creatures.  An evil person of level
equal or less than caster will suffer 100 damage points.

If the victim is higher level than caster, the spell will inflict
(caster_level)d4 damage points, saving throw versus half damage.

See also: DISPEL GOOD
#
DISPEL GOOD

Usage       : cast 'dispel good' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 56

This spell will only affect good creatures.  A good person of level
equal or less than caster will suffer 100 damage points.

If the victim is higher level than caster, the spell will inflict
(caster_level)d4 damage points, saving throw versus half damage.

See also: DISPEL EVIL
#
EARTHQUAKE

Usage       : cast 'earthquake'
Level       : Cleric - 50

This spell will damage everybody except the caster by 1d8+level of
caster hitpoints.
#
ENCHANT WEAPON

Usage       : cast 'enchant weapon' <weapon>
Duration    : Permanent
Level       : Mage - 38

This spell will enchant non-magical (non-modifying) weapons only.  By
non-modifying weapons we refer to weapons that might alter any ability
such as for example damage.  The only way to know if a weapon is 
suitable for enchantment is to fully identify it.

The enchantment will modify the weapon as:

    Level    Hit Roll    Damage

     0..17     +1         +1
    18..19     +2         +1
    20..20+    +2         +2
#
ENERGY DRAIN

Usage       : cast 'energy drain' <victim>
Level       : Vampyre - 34, Mage - 80

This spell does not give much damage, but victims failing their saving
throws will loose up to 40,000 XP points.  You will gain a quarter of
this XP.

Beware that this spell is evil.
#
FIREBALL

Usage       : cast 'fireball' <victim>
Level       : Mage - 86

The mage can conjure up a ball of fire to strike at their target with. 
This is the second most powerful spell a mage can use.

See also: "COLOR SPRAY"
#
HARM

Usage       : cast 'harm' <victim>
Level       : Paladin - 51, Cleric - 71

This spell removes all but 1d4 hitpoints from the victim.  The maximum
number of damage points are 100.  It is not possible to kill using this
spell.
#
HEAL

Usage       : cast 'heal' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 65

Player can now use magical powers to heal themselves or allies in
combat.  Maximum 100 points can be healed.  A victim who is blinded will
also be cured by the heal spell.

See also: "CURE BLINDNESS"
#
INFRAVISION

Usage       : cast 'infravision'
Duration    : 12 hours + level
Level       : Mage - 7, Bard & Vampyre - 9, Cleric - 26, Paladin - 27

Allows the caster to detect the heat given off by objects giving them
the ability to have much better vision in dark conditions.

See also: DETECT INVISIBILITY
#
INVISIBILITY

Usage       : cast 'invisibility' <victim | object>
Duration    : 24 hours, permanent on objects.
Level       : Mage - 15, Vampyre - 20

Makes the target of the spell invisible to everyone except those who
have the "detect invisibility" spell.  Attacking while invisible will
immediately break the spell.

See also: DETECT INVISIBILITY
#
LIGHTNING BOLT

Usage       : cast 'lightning bolt' <victim>
Level       : Mage - 68

A lightning bolt from the sky will strike down onto the mages victim. 
This spell is more powerful than the shocking grasp spell.

See also: SHOCKING GRASP
#
LOCATE OBJECT

Usage       : cast 'locate object' <object>
Level       : Mage - 20, Vampyre - 41

If possible you will know exactly where an object is, or the name of the
person using it.  The maximum number of objects you can simultaneously
locate is your level divided by 2.
#
MAGIC MISSILE

Usage       : cast 'magic missile' <victim>
Level       : Mage, Bard, Vampyre - 1

Causes a bolt of magical energy to be thrown from the casters hands at
the victim.
#
PROTECTION FROM EVIL

Usage       : cast 'protection from evil' [self]
Duration    : 24 hours
Level       : Cleric - 29, Paladin - 66

This spell will protect the target from evil creatures, lowering damage
taken from an evil creature.
#
REMOVE CURSE

Usage       : cast 'remove curse' <victim | object>
Level       : Cleric - 77

Will remove a curse on carried objects or any persons in the room.
#
REMOVE POISON

Usage       : cast 'remove poison' <victim | food | drink> 
Level       : Cleric - 41

Will remove the affects of poison from a victim or an object.

See also: POISON
#
SANCTUARY

Usage       : cast 'sanctuary' [self]
Duration    : 4 hours
Level       : Cleric - 59, Bard - 90, Paladin - 94

When protected by sanctuary you will only receive 1/2 the normal damage
caused by a particular blow.

See also: ARMOR, BLESS
#
SHOCKING GRASP

Usage       : cast 'shocking grasp' <victim>
Level       : Mage - 50

This spell is more powerful than the burning hands spell.

See also: BURNING HANDS
#
STRENGTH

Usage       : cast 'strength' <victim>
Duration    : Level/2 + 4
Level       : Mage - 11

A person will gain 1 strength point per spell (2 points if level of
caster is greater than 18).  Maximum strength is 18/100.
#
SUMMON

Usage       : cast 'summon' <victim>
Level       : Cleric - 38,  Paladin - 98

Will summon a person of the name spoken.  It is not possible to summon
someone of three or more levels above yourself.  If you attempt to
summon a monster, it will get a saving throw.

See also: NOSUMMON
#
WORD OF RECALL

Usage       : cast 'word of recall' 
Level       : Cleric - 47

The caster will be transferred back to his hometown sanctuary.
#
SNEAK

Usage       : sneak
Level       : Thief, Scout - 1

The person can now move without being seen by other players.  This is a
good tactic to use when running by agro creatures.
#
PICK LOCK

Usage       : pick <door>
Level       : Thief - 3

A skilled thief can now pick locks rather than slaying creatures for
keys.  Keep in mind though that not all doors can be picked by even the
most skilled of thieves.
#
BACKSTAB

Usage       : backstab <victim>
Level       : Thief - 9, Scout - 20

A person can now innitiate battle by backstabing their target.  The
backstab will deal more damage than a normal hit and will net more
experience.  You cannot backstab during battle.
#
TAME

Usage       : tame <cvictim>
Duration    : 25 hours
Level       : Warrior - 3, Thief - 12, Scout - 70

Taming a mob will make it easier to be mounted upon.
#
STEAL

Usage       : steal <item> <victim>
Level       : Thief - 20

The thief can now steal objects and or gold from MOBs.
#
HIDE

Usage       : hide
Level       :Scout - 9, Vampyre - 12, Thief - 40

The player can attempt to mask himself by hiding.  The player cannot be
seen by other players unless they can see through your mask of
deception.  Player will remain hidden until action is taken that will
reveal him.
#
TRACK

Usage       : track <target>
Level       : Warrior - 9, Scout - 12, Thief - 55, Paladin - 73
              Bard - 74

Player can now track down a person or monster using this skill.  This
can help find someone in hiding or a mob.
#
SECOND ATTACK

Usage       : Automatic
Level       : Warrior - 20, Scout - 50, Bard - 56, Paladin - 58
              Thief - 65, Vampyre - 84, Cleric - 90, Mage - 98

Player can now strike 2 times per combat round.
#
THIRD ATTACK

Usage       : Automatic
Level       : Warrior - 60, Paladin - 80, Thief & Scout - 85, Bard - 86
              Vampyre - 98

Player can now strike 3 times per combat round.
#
BASH

Usage       : bash <victim>
Level       : Warrior - 45

Warrior can attempt to send their opponent to the ground with a powerful
bash, rendering them unable to strike them or cast spells.
#
RESCUE

Usage       : rescue <target>
Level       : Bard - 80, Warrior - 85

Player can now rescue a person in combat directing them out of harms
way and tanks against the creature.
#
METEOR SWARM

Usage       : c meteor swarm <victim>
Level       : Mage - 92

Player can call upon the heavens to bring down the wrath of a meteor
swarm to fall onto their enemy.
#
CLASS

Port 4000 offers 8 different classes to choose from.  They fall into 3
main categories:  Spellcaster, Fighter, and Nomad.

Fighter:                 Spellcaster:               Nomad:          
  Warrior                  Cleric                     Bard
  Paladin                  Mage                       Scout
                           Vampyre                    Thief

Remort classes:
  Ninja
  Master

See also:  WARRIOR, PALADIN, CLERIC, MAGE, VAMPYRE, BARD, SCOUT, THIEF,
SCOUT
#
RACE

Here is a list of the different races offered by Port 4000 and their
bonuses.
  1) Human      No Modifiers
  2) Dwarf      +2 Con +1 Str -2 Cha -1 Dex
  3) Elf        +2 Int +2 Cha +1 Dex -3 Con -2 Str
  4) Hobbit     +1 Dex -1 Str
  5) Wolf      +1 Dex +1 Cha -1 Con -1 Str
  6) Giant     +3 Str -2 Int -1 Wis
  7) Gnome     +2 Int -1 Wis -1 Dex
  8) Pixie     +2 Dex -2 Str
  9) Gargoyle  +2 Con +1 Str -2 Int -1 Cha
  A) Brownie   +1 Int +1 Dex -2 Cha
  B) Troll     +2 Str -2 Cha
