NOSUMMON

Typing NOSUMMON will prevent other players from summoning you.  To turn
it off simply type NOSUMMON again.

See also:  SUMMON
#
GROUP ARMOR

Usage       : cast 'group armor'
Level       : Cleric - 32, Paladin - 87

The group armor spell will improve your groups AC by 20.
#
WARRIOR

The Fighter is the basic Man-at-Arms. This does not mean, however, that
they are weak. The fighter is the most versatile warrior of the world,
able to wield nearly any weapon found or wear any armor. In addition,
the fighter learns more and more martial skills as he/she increases in
level.

See also:  CLASS, WSKILLS
#
PALADIN

Paladins are holy avengers, those who fight for truth and the church. 
THey are the warriors of the church, strong fighters who are given the
sacred power to know the truth, heal the sick and wounded, and protect
against evil.

See also:  CLASS, PSKILLS
#
BARD

Bards are a jack of all trades, but a master of none.  As a bard you get
skills from every other class, but you are also not able to do many of
the things other classes can.  They rely mostly on using their varied
talents instead of focusing on one area.

See also:  CLASS, BSKILLS
#
VAMPYRE

Vampyres are dark, mystical creatures who have exposed themselves to
mortal sin.  They are a practicioner of the mystical arts, and are also
very adept at trickery and thievery.  Never turn your back on a Vampyre.

See also:  CLASS, VSKILLS
#
MAGE

Mages are mystics whose magic comes from their own indomitable will.
They can create fantastic magics simply by commanding them to happen. As
the mage increases in power, his or her willpower increases
respectively, enabling stronger and more devastating magics to be
unleashed upon the Mage's foes.

See also:  CLASS, MSKILLS
#
CLERIC

The clerics are the religious sect of the world.  Members of the cleric
guilds are given the wisdom of peace, blessing, and healing, as well as
certain spells used to wreak havoc on the unrighteous.  Clerics are more
skilled in combat than all save the warriors, but can only wield whips
and/or blunt and bludgeoning weapons.

See also:  CLASS, CSKILLS
#
THIEF

The thieves of the world are those who rely on guile and trickery
to gain their end, rather than brute force or magical might.  To
that end, thieves have a wide range of unusual skills to suit their
needs, and are well suited for exploring areas that others cannot reach.

See also:  CLASS, TSKILLS
#
SCOUT

Scouts fill a variety of roles.  Some scouts are rugged wilderness
adventurers who seek out uncharted lands, and are idealy suited to
handly many different situations.  Others chose to infiltrate enemy
castles and fortresses for spying purposes.  Scouts are well suited for
either task, and are also usually very good fighters if they are forced
to.

See also:  CLASS, SSKILLS
